    "source_commit": "8fec14c",
    "notes": [
      "JS lifecycle oracle proof for source Game.onRoundEnd resolving round score into persistent match score across two all-present 3P rounds.",
      "The harness starts with bonuses disabled and max_score 3, forces avatars 3 and 2 into same-frame wall deaths in round 1, and keeps avatar 1 on a slow safe path so avatar 1 survives the terminal source update and reaches persistent score 2.",
      "The first warmdown emits game:stop and round:new because no present avatar is uniquely at or above max_score.",
      "After the second warmup and delayed PrintManager.start timers, the harness repeats the controlled deaths so avatar 1 reaches persistent score 4; the second warmdown emits game:stop and end, with no following round:new.",
      "This is only the focused 3P all-present multi-round match-end proof; it does not claim 4P, present/non-present broadening, removeAvatar, vector/full lifecycle, production self-play, bonuses, wire, or pixels."
    ]
  },
